{"id":"46889991","title":"SwiftMailer and SMTP logger: how to get output using disk spooler?","body":"<p>I'm using Swift Mailer with the Logger plugin to get SMTP output, and everything is working.</p>

<pre><code>$smtp_transport = (new Swift_SmtpTransport('mail.mydomain.com', 25))
        -&gt;setUsername('my_smtp_username')
        -&gt;setPassword('my_smtp_pwd');

$mailer = new Swift_Mailer($smtp_transport);
$logger = new Swift_Plugins_Loggers_ArrayLogger();
$mailer-&gt;registerPlugin(new Swift_Plugins_LoggerPlugin($logger));

$message = (new Swift_Message('My subject'))
        -&gt;setFrom('from@mydomain.com', 'My Name')
        -&gt;setTo('to@otherdomain.com')
        -&gt;setBody('My body', 'text/html');

$mailer-&gt;send($message);

echo $logger-&gt;dump();
</code></pre>

<p>The next step is to implement a sort of queue. I tried to use Swift Mailer's disk spooler and I think it works great for my needs.</p>

<pre><code>$spool = new Swift_FileSpool('/path/to/spool');
$spool-&gt;setMessageLimit(3);

$spool_transport = new Swift_SpoolTransport($spool);
$mailer = new Swift_Mailer($spool_transport);
$logger = new Swift_Plugins_Loggers_ArrayLogger();
$mailer-&gt;registerPlugin(new Swift_Plugins_LoggerPlugin($logger));

$message = (new Swift_Message('My subject'))
        -&gt;setFrom('from@mydomain.com', 'My Name')
        -&gt;setTo('to@otherdomain.com')
        -&gt;setBody('My body', 'text/html');

/* Not really sent, just sent to disk spool */
$mailer-&gt;send($message);

$smtp_transport = (new Swift_SmtpTransport('mail.mydomain.com', 25))
        -&gt;setUsername('my_smtp_username')
        -&gt;setPassword('my_smtp_pwd');

/* Now it has been sent */
$spool-&gt;flushQueue($smtp_transport);

/* But I lost SMTP debug... */
echo $logger-&gt;dump();
</code></pre>

<p>But I lost any SMTP debug!
I tried using 2 different instances of SwiftMailer, but the result is the same: the method flushQueue doesn't fill any log, so the SMTP output is lost.</p>

<p>Is there a way to solve?
